    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/979.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 439.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 16th instant, by which you inform the Department
                    that reports have come to the Government of Mexico that Mexican insurgents
                    intend to dress like soldiers of the Mexican Federal Army and fire on American
                    soldiers performing guard duty on the frontier.</p>
                <p>Your note has been copied to the War Department and the Department of Justice for
                    their information.</p>
                <p>Thanking [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
